==English==

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[wyrt]]''.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /wə:t/

===Noun===
'''wort'''
# liquid exract from the ground malt and grain soaked in hot water, the mash, as one of the steps in making [[beer]].
# any of various [[plant]]s or [[herb]]s.
#: The word is usually used in combination to refer to specific plants, e.g. ''[[St. John's wort|St. John’s wort]]''; however, it may be used on its own as a generic term.

